definition.value: A organophosphate oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the three diphosphate OH groups of tuberculosinyl diphosphate.
An organosulfonate oxoanion that is the dianion of sulfoacetic acid arising from deprotonation of carboxylic acid and sulfo groups.
The dianion resulting from the removal of the two acidic protons from the phosphate group of (2S)-2-hydroxy-3-oxobutyl phosphate.
Dicarboxylate anion arising from deprotonation of both carboxylic acid groups of iminoaspartic acid.
Dianion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate group of 2,3-bis-O-(geranylgeranyl)-sn-glycerol 1-phosphate.
Dianion arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of CDP-2,3-bis-O-(geranylgeranyl)-sn-glycerol.
N(6)-Dihydrolipoyl-L-lysine residue protonated on the nitrogen at C-2.
A member of the class of psoralens that is psoralen substituted by a prenyloxy group at position 8. Isolated from Angelica dahurica and Angelica koreana, it acts as a acetylcholinesterase inhibitor.
Dianion arising from deprotonation of both carboxylic acid groups of 2-methyl-3-oxosuccinic acid.
Trianion arising from deprotonation of all three carboxylic acid groups of (2S,3S)-2-methylcitric acid.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 7,8-dihydro-D-neopterin 2',3'-cyclic phosphate, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH.
A secondary aliphatic amine protonated on nitrogen.
An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate acid of N-(3-acetamidopropyl)-4-aminobutanal arising from deprotonation of the secondary amino function.
Dianion of hydroxypyruvaldehyde phosphate arising from deprotonation of both of the phosphate OH groups.
Dianion of 1-deoxy-D-threo-hexo-2,5-diulose 6-phosphate arising from deprotonation of both of the phosphate OH groups.
Dianion of N(2)-succinyl-L-citrulline arsing from deprotonation of both carboxylic acid groups.
A 5-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of futalosine.
A 5-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of dehypoxanthine futalosine.
